Politics  Policy:
   Voter Optimism Edges Up
   On Economy, Poll Finds
The change in attitudes may partly reflect the sharp cut
in interest rates pushed through by the Federal Reserve in
December. But ironically, the poll showed that 23% of
respondents felt their personal finances had been hurt by
lower interest rates, while only 19% felt they had been
helped. In particular, elderly people, many of whom live off
interest and dividend income, responded that they had been
hurt by the cut in interest rates.